  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis scalar transport is modelled via the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law formulation; shear-stress histories are extracted along Lagrangian particle tracks seeded at the pump inlet. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device) was adopted in alignment with FDA guidance on blood-contacting device simulation. Methodological grounding for the power-law exponent calibration follows the approach described in the peer-reviewed study indexed at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which characterises in-vitro erythrocyte fragility under controlled shear exposure and provides the empirical basis for the damage accumulation coefficients used here.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
